Package net.dean.jraw.models

Contains models used in JRAW.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Account
    Represents a redditor's account.
    AccountPreferences  
    Captcha
    Represents a Captcha
    Comment
    Represents a comment on a link
    CompactComment
    Represents a comment as shown in a response by POST /api/morechildren.
    Contribution
    This class provides a way to wrap Submission, Comment, and Message together.
    EmbeddedMedia
    This class represents a simplified version of oEmbed data that includes embedded HTML
    FauxListing<T extends RedditObject>
    This class is a "hacky" way to represent a Listing
    Flair
    Represents the effective flair of an author or a submission
    FlairTemplate
    Represents a single flair template on a subreddit
    JsonModel
    This class provides an abstract model for retrieving data from a JSON node, although not necessarily relating to the Reddit API.
    KarmaBreakdown  
    KarmaBreakdown.Summary
    Represents one subreddit in a karma breakdown
    Listing<T extends RedditObject>
    Represents a listing of Things.
    LiveThread
    Represents a live thread.
    LiveUpdate
    Represents an update in a live thread
    LiveUpdate.Embed
    Represents embedded data in a LiveUpdate
    LoggedInAccount
    Represents a the authenticated user's account
    Message
    This class represents a private message sent from one user to another
    ModAction
    Represents an administrative action from a moderator of a subreddit
    More
    This class represents a list of Thing IDs that could not be downloaded because there were too many to list.
    MultiReddit
    Represents a collection of subreddits.
    OEmbed
    Represents media provided by an oEmbed-style JSON object.
    OEmbed.Thumbnail
    Represents an oEmbed thumbnail
    PublicContribution
    This class is used to separate public contributions (submissions and comments) from private contributions (messages)
    RedditObject
    Provides another layer of abstraction between "normal" models (as seen here) like Submission and "abnormal" models like Listing and More.
    RenderStringPair
    This class represents a String that has a raw, unformatted version in Markdown, and a formatted version in HTML.
    Submission
    Represents content that the user has submitted, whether that be a self post or a link.
    Subreddit
    This class represents a Subreddit such as /r/pics.
    Thing
    Represents the base class of all objects defined in the Reddit API, except for "Listing" and "more".
    UserRecord
    This class represents a small bit of data relevant to moderation logs such as banned users, accepted contributors, and moderators.
    WikiPage
    Represents a wiki page.
    WikiPageSettings
    Represents the settings of a wiki page

    JsonProperty

Package net.dean.jraw.models Description

Contains models used in JRAW. Most classes will extend JsonModel, but they are not required to.
